Git Installation:

Download git executable from https://git-scm.com/download/

Setting up account and creating repository:

1) create a account in github.com
2) login with your credentials
3) select new repository option
4) enter the details for creating a new repository
5)

 …or create a new repository on the command line

echo "# Chef_devops_training" >> README.md
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git remote add origin https://github.com/rakeshkorukonda/Chef_devops_training.git
git push -u origin master

…or push an existing repository from the command line

git remote add origin https://github.com/rakeshkorukonda/Chef_devops_training.git
git push -u origin master


To download or clone a repository:

git clone <URL>

git clone https://github.com/rakeshkorukonda/Chef_devops_training.git



git status 
(this will show status of repisitory. A local repository is directory where git folder is placed.
this git folder will monitor the other files that are in the same directory as git folder has places)

git status will show any new files are added to repisotory where git folder is there

for eg--> if you added a new text file in directory say new.txt

git status command will show the files that are newly added to repository.
which is new.txt
--------------------
git add .
-----------------------
git commit
--------------------
now new.txt is also added to git folder

push it to central repisitory

